\\text{iso}}^{1/8}E_{\\text{p}}^{1/2}/(T_{90})^{1/4}$ to estimate $\\Gamma $.\nFinally, the different distributions for $E_{\\text{p}}$ and $E_{\\text{iso}}$,\nand the consistent efficiency exist for the short GRBs. Besides, we give a\nnatural explanation of the extended emission ($\\epsilon _{\\gamma }\\lesssim\n50\\%$) and the main pulse ($\\epsilon _{\\gamma }\\gtrsim 50\\%$).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Apr 2022 10:55:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 12 Dec 2022 11:51:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-13"}
